title: Sardar Sarfraz Chakar Domki wins PB-08 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan People’s Party Parliamentarians (PPPP) candidate Sardar Sarfraz Chakar Domki has won the Balochistan Assembly election from PB-08, Sibbi by securing 27,677 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was an Independent candidate Mir Muhammad Asghar Khan Marri who bagged 23,769 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 47.00 percent.
